1 position in ethanol production and the processing of agricultural
2 products into ethanol, ethanol coproducts, or products derived from
3 ethanol or ethanol coproducts that improve air quality, strengthen energy
4 security, increase demand for agricultural products, provide consumer
5 choice, and displace products produced from petroleum. The Nebraska
6 Ethanol Board shall be the state agency for such purpose. The Legislature
7 also recognizes the need for a statewide approach to identify and attract
8 agricultural processing opportunities that support the Nebraska ethanol
9 industry, the need to participate in programs of research, education,
10 market development, and promotion of ethanol, ethanol coproducts, or
11 products derived from ethanol or ethanol coproducts, and the need to
12 provide subject matter expertise related to policy and regulatory affairs
13 for ethanol, ethanol coproducts, or products derived from ethanol or
14 ethanol coproducts. It is hereby declared to be the public policy of the
15 state that, in order to safeguard life, health, property, and public
16 welfare of its citizens, the production, sale, and use of motor fuel and
17 the pollution caused by certain components of motor fuel are matters
18 affecting the public interest and that a statewide emphasis on the
19 production and use of motor fuel containing agricultural ethyl alcohol as
20 a substitute for polluting components is necessary for the reduction of
21 pollution and will further serve as an incentive for the agricultural
22 economy in this state. The Legislature further recognizes that a fuel
23 crisis is pending in the nation and that the development of an additional
24 source of fuel will provide an energy and environmental benefit to the
25 citizens of this state and to the future economic growth of Nebraska.
