6 one hundred fifty thousand dollars shall be prorated, based on the number
7 of months the fee is collected, whenever the fee is collected for only a
8 portion of a year. The amount deducted and withheld for costs shall be
9 deposited in the Petroleum Release Remedial Action Collection Fund which
10 is hereby created. The Petroleum Release Remedial Action Collection Fund
11 shall be appropriated to the Department of Revenue, except that transfers
12 may be made from the fund to the General Fund at the direction of the
13 Legislature. Any money in the Petroleum Release Remedial Action
14 Collection Fund available for investment shall be invested by the state
15 investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the
16 Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
17 (5) The Department of Revenue shall collect the fee imposed by
18 subsection (1) of this section.
19 Sec. 13. Sections 1, 2, 3, 7, 12, and 15 of this act become
20 operative on October 1, 2026. The other sections of this act become
21 operative on their effective date.
22 Sec. 14. Original sections 66-1331, 66-1332, 66-1333, 66-1337,
23 66-1338, and 66-1340, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, and section
24 66-1335, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, are repealed.
25 Sec. 15. Original section 66-726, Reissue Revised Statutes of
26 Nebraska, and sections 66-489, 66-739, 66-1334, and 66-1521, Revised
27 Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, are repealed.
28 Sec. 16. The following sections are outright repealed: Sections
29 66-1342, 66-1344.01, 66-1345, 66-1345.05, and 66-1348, Reissue Revised
30 Statutes of Nebraska, and section 66-1344, Revised Statutes Supplement,
31 2025.
